BACKEND:Node.js

I want to detect suspicious attacks like brute force attack, dos and ddos
Do active scanning of network(IP address)

The maximum number of attempts for login is 3 before locking that account for half an hour and alerts the user in the dashboard next time he log's in

This project should be mapped to MITRE Framework

1.Brute Force Detection
If login attempts > 3 → account locked for 30 minutes
Generates alert
Maps to:
MITRE ID: T1110 (Brute Force)

2.DoS / Traffic Spike Detection (Simulated)
High number of requests from a single IP in short time
Flag as suspicious
⚠️ Important:
You are simulating DoS, not performing real attacks
3.Suspicious IP Tracking
Tracks frequency of requests per IP
Flags abnormal behavior


MITRE ATT&CK Mapping (CORE FEATURE)

Each detected attack is mapped to:

Technique ID
Attack category

Example:
Attack: Brute Force
MITRE Technique: T1110
Tactic: Credential Access
